"version": "1.0.2",
"title": "8345: servanthood, and worship of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8345: servanthood, and worship of god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The biblical understanding of servanthood has its foundation in people serving God in worship. The terms for “service” and “worship” are often interchangeable.</p>\n<h2>Worship is a central aspect of serving God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:12\">EXO 3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:23\">EXO 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:1\">EXO 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:20\">EXO 8:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:8\">EXO 10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:27\">JOS 22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps100:2\">PSA 100:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:22\">PSA 102:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:8\">LUK 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Worship entails total obedience, not merely correct religious observances</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:12-Deut10:13\">DEU 10:12–10:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:22-Amos5:24\">AMO 5:22–5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:6-Mic6:8\">MIC 6:6–6:8</a></p>\n<h2>Worship and service to God must be exclusive</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:10\">MAT 4:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:8\">LUK 4:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13\">DEU 6:13</a></p>\n<h2>Serving false gods</h2>\n<h3>Worshipping false gods forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:3-Exod20:5\">EXO 20:3–20:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:8-Deut5:9\">DEU 5:8–5:9</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:24\">EXO 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:14\">EXO 34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:7\">JOS 23:7</a></p>\n<h3>Warnings against serving false gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:19-2Chr7:20\">2CH 7:19–7:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:3-Deut7:4\">DEU 7:3–7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:16\">JOS 23:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:20\">JOS 24:20</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of idolatrous service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:31\">1KI 16:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:11\">JDG 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:13\">JDG 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:33\">2KI 17:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:20\">JER 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:10\">JER 11:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:25\">ROM 1:25</a></p>\n<h3>Refusal to serve false gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:12\">DAN 3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:16-Josh24:18\">JOS 24:16–24:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:18\">DAN 3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:28-Dan3:29\">DAN 3:28–3:29</a></p>\n<h3>Judgment for serving false gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:11-Judg10:13\">JDG 10:11–10:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:6-Judg10:10\">JDG 10:6–10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:30-Ezek20:38\">EZK 20:30–20:38</a></p>\n<h2>The service of the Levites and the priesthood</h2>\n<h3>Consecration of the priesthood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:1\">EXO 29:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:1\">EXO 28:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:41\">EXO 28:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:44\">EXO 29:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:12-Exod40:16\">EXO 40:12–40:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:9-Num3:13\">NUM 3:9–3:13</a></p>\n<h3>Service in the Tent of Meeting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:3\">NUM 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:23\">NUM 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:30\">NUM 4:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:35\">NUM 4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:39\">NUM 4:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:43\">NUM 4:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:7\">NUM 18:7</a></p>\n<h3>Service in the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:2-1Chr23:5\">1CH 23:2–23:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:24-1Chr23:32\">1CH 23:24–23:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr24:3\">1CH 24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr24:5\">1CH 24:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr24:19\">1CH 24:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:1\">1CH 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:6-1Chr25:8\">1CH 25:6–25:8</a> <em>musicians and singers</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:12\">1CH 26:12</a> <em>gatekeepers</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:20\">1CH 26:20</a> <em>treasurers</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:29-1Chr26:32\">1CH 26:29–26:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:7\">EZR 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:20\">EZR 8:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh7:46\">NEH 7:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh7:60\">NEH 7:60</a></p>\n<h3>The promise of restored service in the new temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:15\">EZK 44:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:10-Ezek44:14\">EZK 44:10–44:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:24\">EZK 44:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:5\">EZK 45:5</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of priestly service</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:5\">LUK 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:8-Luke1:10\">LUK 1:8–1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:23\">LUK 1:23</a></p>\n<h3>The true service of Jesus Christ as high priest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1-Heb8:2\">HEB 8:1–8:2</a></strong> <em>Hebrews sees the OT priesthood and its services as superseded by Jesus Christ.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:3-Heb8:6\">HEB 8:3–8:6</a></p>\n<h2>The Christian's life as an act of worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:6\">REV 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:10\">REV 5:10</a></p>",
